annotation={E-Stat is a widely used portal site for accessing Japanese governmental statistical data. Began operation in 2008. e-Stat currently hosts about 690 surveys from about 30 governmental agencies. This paper chooses several features that impede users' ability to search and retrieve datasets, and proposes solutions: 1) The hierarchical structure of item and content names, 2) Synonyms, 3) The variety of punctuation symbols}
